              Guide Details</font></b></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2">
              </td>
          </tr>

<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>VHALEN NOSTROLO</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Necromancer</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">31</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Karana, South</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Near a well (loc -50 -120)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">30 to 39</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Vhalen is a Bard that pretty much hits like a Monk.  Fast and powerful, he can deal up to 150 points of damage per round with his two attacks.  He spawns just by the small pond close to loc -200,-200 every 7 minutes.
<br><br>
I will break down this strategy for players below level 34 and past level 34.
<br><br>
<b>Levels 30 to 33</b>:<br>
Well, below level 34 you don't have Root or Invoke Fear so you will have to rely on your pet.  You can hunt Vhalen without a pet, but it is safer to have one.  So, find Vhalen, sit a little far away from him and cast a pet.  Med to full and buff him with Intensify Death.  Once you are ready, get within casting range and pull with Darkness.  Immediately send your pet after him.  If Darkness was resisted, recast it until it sticks.  Now you have two options.  First, you can try Fearing Vhalen.  If Fear is successful, the battle ahead won't be a hard one.  The problem is at level 30-33, you will be using a low level Fear spell that will be often resisted.  You won't have time to recast Fear a few times.  By the time you pull it off, your pet will be severely hurt and you will be a little low on mana.  So, if you want to try it, do it once or twice maximum.  If it is resisted, move to the second option.  If not, simply cast Boil Blood and Spirit Tap him till dead.
<br><br>
The second option is a little safer in my opinion.  After you pulled with Darkness and sent your pet to battle, cast Boil Blood and move a little close to him.  He will start following you.  Move back slowly but fast enough so that he doesn't catch up with you.  By doing this, he will constantly try to reach you and won't return fire against your pet.  Every now and then, turn around and run to a casting distance.  Spirit Tap him and repeat the process.  You will be close to out of mana by the time Vhalen dies.
<br><br>
<b>Levels 34 to 39</b>:<br>
Now you have root and Invoke Fear, which makes the battles are a lot easier.  And the XP is better also since you won't need a pet anymore.  Once again, you could do it two ways.
<br><br>
First, you can use Root.  Pull with Root and if resisted, reapply until it sticks.  Once you get it off, move back to a safe casting distance and start stacking DoTs.  Cast Venom of the Snake and Boil Blood, reapplying Root when needed.  Vampiric Curse him when close to dead and finish him off with Spirit Tap.  If you got Vampiric Curse on, cast Call of Bones to speed up your meding process.
<br><br>
The second way you can do this is by using Invoke Fear.  Pull with Darkness, reapplying if resisted.  As soon as it sticks, cast Invoke Fear.  Since this is a level 34 spell, it will be rarely resisted.  When you get it off, go ahead and cast Venom of the Snake and Boil Blood.  Just go after him and cast an occasional Spirit Tap to speed up the process.  Reapply Invoke Fear when needed.  You can even med every now and then during the battle since Vhalen will be pretty much helpless.  Cast Vampiric Curse before Vhalen goes down and finish him off with Spirit Tap.  Remember, Root will cancel the Darkness effect so if you are going for this strategy, do not cast Root.
<br><br>
Well, there you go.  Vhalen is pretty good for those looking for some quick XP.  Loot is pretty poor though.  He usually drops a few gold pieces and a maximum of 4 plat per kill.  He also drops a 2g Flute, so don't even bother keeping them.
<br><br>
A few comments.   You won't be fighting close to any zones, so don't try running to zone unless you got a good head start.  But the real good option in case a battle goes wrong is to Feign Death.  Since Vhalen is a level 30 mob, Feign Death should always work.  So, if you see you are loosing the fight, simply move far away from Vhalen spawning point and Feign.  He will forget about you and return to the pond.  Wait a little while, get up, med, and do it again.  If you are not careless, you shouldn't die here, ever.  One last thing.  Vhalen will hurt your faction with the League of Antonican Bards.  But as Necros, why do we care? :)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Skyshade (Bristlebane)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>8.3</b> (average of <b>3</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE